Localization.Name: Greycat Industrial
Localization.Description: A trusted manufacturer of industrial tools since 2337, the company’s extensive line of industrial equipment and armor make it one of the most respected brand names around. Greycat has remained a UEE staple for centuries thanks to their streamlined-yet-inventive designs, exacting safety standards, and a diverse product line.

Localization.Name: Pyro RYT Multi-Tool
Localization.Description:
ATTACHMENTS SOLD SEPARATELY!

Manufacturer: Greycat Industrial
Item Type: Utility
Class: Gadget

Magazine Size: Integrated Battery
Rate of Fire: N / A (Beam)
Effective Range: 0.5 m

The Pyro from Greycat Industrial is a pistol-sized power tool for the modern space engineer that is capable of charging, cutting and patching; achieving a multitude of uses thanks to its wide assortment of attachments. Perfect for making a tough job a little bit easier.

Localization.Name: OreBit Mining Attachment
Localization.Description:
MUST BUY BASE MULTI-TOOL TO USE: "Pyro RYT Multi-Tool"

Manufacturer: Greycat Industrial
Item Type: Multi-Tool Attachment
Class: Mining

The OreBit attachment turns Greycat's Pyro RYT Multi-Tool into a handheld mining machine. It can scan rocks to find worthwhile deposits and then liberate the lode with its powerful mining laser. Next time you're planetside, be sure you bring this attachment or risk leaving easy credits behind.

Localization.Name: TruHold Tractor Beam Attachment
Localization.Description:
MUST BUY BASE MULTI-TOOL TO USE: "Pyro RYT Multi-Tool"

Manufacturer: Greycat Industrial
Item Type: Multi-Tool Attachment
Class: Tractor Beam

Whether your feet are on the floor or floating in zero-G, the TruHold attachment for the Pyro RYT Multi-Tool makes lifting and positioning items easier than ever. With its impressive and efficient pull/draw ratio and easy-to-read range finder, the TruHold can be used solo or paired with other beams to tackle heavier targets. Plus, the TruHold has the added benefit of functioning as a personal zero-G traversal device when coupled to an object with a high enough mass.
